Hello Community!  

I hope this is the right section for this thread:  

I'm currently experimenting with my multiboot usb-stick. What I have this far:  
Actual Grub4Dos wich boots  
PartedMagic, MemTest86+, Backtrack, Avira Recue CD, DBAN and some others.  
+ BartPE with FBWF-filter  

Now my question: All Applications work on CD / DVD without problems. (FBWF in BartPE is enabled and there is no need for a RAM-Drive anymore + virtual writing to CD / DVD)  

When I'm trying to get BartPE to work with my USB-flashdrive I have to rename "i386" to "minint" and copy "SETUPLDR.BIN" as "NTLDR" to root of the stick and copy "ntdetect.com" to root...  
I think the error does not lie within these steps because BartPE is booting to desktop.  

The BartPE has XPE, Driverpacks and FBWF enabled. The Version of FBWF is 2.0.965.  

The Problem is that BartPE is booting up without the FBWF-driver enabled. (I want this feature to prevent wearout of my USB-drive)  
Interesting is also that once loaded my BartPE doesnt recognise other Harddrives and "compmgmt.msc" wont start.  

My Plugin looks like this:  

